---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Orkin Alternative NYC Restaurant | Cloakd"
  description="Orkin's Restaurant Precision Protection handles the active colony. The replacement cycle that keeps rodents coming back four weeks after treatment is outside its scope. Here's what closes that gap."
  path="/vs/orkin"
>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── HERO ── -->
  <section class="pt-20 pb-24 px-6 max-w-6xl mx-auto">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-6">
        Orkin vs. Cloakd
      </p>
      <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-[1.08] tracking-tight mb-8">
        Orkin's Restaurant Precision Protection clears the active colony.<br />
        What fills the territory four weeks later is a different problem.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-[#1c1814]/70 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
        Orkin has been handling commercial rodent control for over a century.
        Their Restaurant Precision Protection program — licensed treatment,
        entry point sealing, preventive protocol — removes what's present.
        It doesn't change how fast the replacement population forms after
        the colony is gone. That's not a failure of Orkin's execution.
        It's a structural limitation of what standard pest control addresses.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── WHAT ORKIN COVERS ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6 bg-[#f0ebe0]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">
        What Restaurant Precision Protection covers
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-6 max-w-2xl">
        A century of commercial rodent control. Still limited by the same biology.
      </h2>

      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-start">
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/65 leading-relaxed">
            Orkin's Restaurant Precision Protection is built for foodservice
            compliance — licensed pest management professional service,
            DOHMH documentation, sealing gaps down to a quarter-inch for
            rats and dime-sized for mice, and a scheduled treatment program.
            For restaurants with active infestations, it handles the immediate
            problem correctly.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/65 leading-relaxed">
            The cycle that keeps the problem recurring is not about how
            the treatment is executed. Norway rats in NYC detect empty
            territory within days of a colony being removed. A new group
            moves in along the same travel paths, exploits the same entry
            points, and establishes harborage in the same locations.
            Treatment happens again. The cycle resets.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/65 leading-relaxed">
            For NYC restaurant operators with active DOHMH violation history,
            passing one inspection doesn't change the timing risk for the
            next unannounced visit. What changes that risk is slowing how
            fast the replacement population builds.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          {[
            {
              label: 'What Orkin covers',
              items: [
                'Licensed PMP treatment under Restaurant Precision Protection',
                'Entry point sealing and exclusion work',
                'Scheduled visit documentation for DOHMH compliance',
                'Preventive protocol and sanitation guidance',
                '24/7 availability and next-day scheduling',
              ],
              positive: true,
            },
            {
              label: 'What standard treatment leaves open',
              items: [
                'Replacement colony forming 4–8 weeks after knockdown',
                'Documented population decline for DOHMH re-inspection',
                'Monthly track count data showing 90-day trend',
                'Fertility management to reduce replacement rate',
              ],
              positive: false,
            },
          ].map(({ label, items, positive }) => (
            <div class={`rounded-xl p-6 ${positive ? 'bg-white border border-[#1c1814]/8' : 'bg-white border border-[#c96a3a]/15'}`}>
              <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#1c1814]/45 mb-4">{label}</p>
              <div class="space-y-3">
                {items.map((item) => (
                  <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                    <div class={`w-5 h-5 rounded-full flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center mt-0.5 ${positive ? 'bg-[#7aab7e]/15' : 'bg-[#1c1814]/8'}`}>
                      {positive
                        ? <svg width="10" height="8" viewBox="0 0 10 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 4L3.5 6.5L9 1" stroke="#5e9263" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
                        : <svg width="8" height="8" viewBox="0 0 8 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1L7 7M7 1L1 7" stroke="#1c1814" stroke-opacity="0.3" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                      }
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/70 leading-relaxed">{item}</p>
                  </div>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── COMPARISON TABLE ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">
        Side-by-side comparison
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-12 max-w-2xl">
        Orkin vs. Cloakd 90-day program
      </h2>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-[#1c1814]/10">
              <th class="py-4 pr-6 text-sm font-semibold text-[#1c1814]/45 uppercase tracking-widest w-1/3">Feature</th>
              <th class="py-4 pr-6 text-sm font-semibold text-[#1c1814]/45 uppercase tracking-widest w-1/3">Orkin</th>
              <th class="py-4 text-sm font-semibold text-[#c96a3a] uppercase tracking-widest w-1/3">Cloakd (added layer)</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {[
              ['Treatment method', 'Restaurant Precision Protection — licensed knockdown, exclusion, scheduled visits', 'Evolve fertility management on top of existing treatment — reduces replacement colony formation'],
              ['Monitoring', 'Scheduled service reports', 'Monthly track count plates at every station — 90-day documented trend'],
              ['Replacement cycle', 'Cleared at treatment, rebuilds 4–8 weeks later', 'Replacement population forms at reduced rate — density declines over 90 days'],
              ['DOHMH compliance record', 'Licensed PMP service documentation', 'Written monthly monitoring reports — 90-day trend line for inspector'],
              ['Re-inspection risk', 'Dependent on timing of next inspection vs. last treatment', 'Reduced — documented declining population, not cycling'],
              ['Works with existing vendor', 'Is your existing vendor', 'Yes — Orkin handles Phase 1, Cloakd adds the fertility layer'],
            ].map(([feature, orkin, cloakd]) => (
              <tr class="border-b border-[#1c1814]/8">
                <td class="py-4 pr-6 text-base font-semibold text-[#1c1814]">{feature}</td>
                <td class="py-4 pr-6 text-base text-[#1c1814]/60 leading-relaxed">{orkin}</td>
                <td class="py-4 text-base text-[#1c1814]/70 leading-relaxed">{cloakd}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── FIELD DATA ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6 bg-[#f0ebe0]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">
        What the fertility layer produces
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-12 max-w-2xl">
        The same knockdown, plus a documented declining trend.
      </h2>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
        {[
          { value: '79%', label: 'reduction in rodent track presence', sub: 'Location A — 5-month urban building deployment, Aug 2025 to Jan 2026', color: '#7aab7e' },
          { value: '88%', label: 'drop in track density at the same site', sub: 'Tracks per monitoring plate declined even at stations with residual activity', color: '#7aab7e' },
          { value: '50%+', label: 'reduction at a second independent site', sub: 'Same 5-month period, different urban building profile', color: '#7aab7e' },
        ].map(({ value, label, sub, color }) => (
          <div class="bg-white border border-[#1c1814]/8 rounded-xl p-6">
            <p class="text-5xl font-bold mb-3" style={`color:${color}`}>{value}</p>
            <p class="text-base font-semibold text-[#1c1814] leading-snug mb-2">{label}</p>
            <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/60 leading-relaxed">{sub}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-[#1c1814]/40 max-w-2xl">
        Source: <a href="https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/senestech-reports-significant-reductions-in-rodent-activity-following-evolve-deployments-in-urban-field-studies-302691116.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-[#1c1814]/65 transition-colors">SenesTech, Inc. — February 18, 2026</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── WHO SHOULD USE EACH ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">
        How to think about it
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-12 max-w-2xl">
        Orkin handles the treatment. Cloakd handles the replacement cycle.
      </h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-[#f0ebe0] rounded-xl p-8">
          <p class="text-base font-semibold text-[#1c1814] mb-4">Orkin alone is sufficient if:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            {[
              'You have a single active infestation with no recurring citation history',
              'Your DOHMH inspection timing has been consistently favorable post-treatment',
              'You need immediate licensed treatment and service documentation',
              'Your building doesn\'t have the density pressure that drives fast replacement',
            ].map((item) => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[#7aab7e] flex-shrink-0 mt-2"></div>
                <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/65">{item}</p>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-[#f0ebe0] rounded-xl p-8">
          <p class="text-base font-semibold text-[#1c1814] mb-4">Add Cloakd if:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            {[
              'You\'ve been cited for 04K or 04L more than once in 24 months',
              'You need a documented 90-day trend line for a DOHMH re-inspection',
              'Your inspection risk is tied to treatment timing — the window problem',
              'You need the monitoring record that shows active management, not just a service receipt',
            ].map((item) => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[#c96a3a]/50 flex-shrink-0 mt-2"></div>
                <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/65">{item}</p>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── CTA ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6 bg-[#f0ebe0]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-6">
          Keep Orkin. Add the layer that addresses the replacement cycle.
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/65 leading-relaxed mb-8">
          Tell us about your property and how long the recurring problem
          has been running. We'll outline exactly what the 90-day program
          adds on top of your existing service.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
          <a
            href="/get-started"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-7 py-4 text-base font-semibold rounded bg-[#b85530] text-[#faf8f4] hover:bg-[#c96a3a] transition-colors"
          >
            Start the 90-day program
          </a>
          <a
            href="/dohmh-rodent-violation-nyc"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-7 py-4 text-base font-medium rounded border border-[#1c1814]/15 text-[#1c1814]/70 hover:text-[#1c1814] hover:border-[#1c1814]/25 transition-colors"
          >
            DOHMH violation codes
          </a>
          <a
            href="/why-it-keeps-coming-back"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-7 py-4 text-base font-medium rounded border border-[#1c1814]/15 text-[#1c1814]/70 hover:text-[#1c1814] hover:border-[#1c1814]/25 transition-colors"
          >
            Why it keeps coming back
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>
